{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PmQqQMjnqJoyhvrM7sRmca","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need to write the files. Let me set up the todos and write everything.\n\nLet me plan the files to write:\n1. `apps/resumeai/Dockerfile.template` - Multi-stage Next.js build with standalone mode\n2. `apps/resumeai/lzc-manifest.yml` - Multi-service: web + mongo sidecar\n3. `apps/resumeai/lzc-build.yml` - Minimal build config\n4. `apps/resumeai/lzc-deploy-params.yml` - Clerk keys, Gemini key, login credentials\n\n\n5. `apps/resumeai/README.md` - Documentation\n6. `apps/resumeai/icon.png` - Placeholder PNG (base64 decode)\n7. `registry/repos/resumeai.json` - Registry config\n8. `registry/repos/index.json` - Add resumeai entry\n\nI'll write these in parallel where possible. The key design decisions are using `upstream_with_target_template` as the build strategy, setting up web and mongo services with the web container built from source and mongo using the official mongo:7 image, exposing port 3000 for the Next.js app, and configuring the MongoDB connection URI.\n\nNow I'm setting up the authentication and API integrations—Clerk with public and secret keys as deploy parameters, Gemini with an API key, and passwordless login using the built-in simple injection strategy. I'm using `commit_sha` for the check strategy since there aren't proper Docker releases, and only targeting the web image for builds since mongo is just a sidecar. For the manifest template variables, I need to reference the pressyard example's syntax with `{{ index .U \"db_password\" }}` and use `id` as the key for deploy parameters.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7134,"cache_read_input_tokens":78931,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7134},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8885b858-35f1-4392-9afa-5fc75e8538ec","uuid":"78414cd3-2686-4d06-beb7-94d3fccae796"}
