{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NPS44y29jcz1ZsLczgY9oo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 7 files written. Everything looks correct.\n\n---\n\n**PLANNER: done**\n\n**Build strategy chosen:** `upstream_with_target_template`\n\n**Files written / modified:**\n\n| File | Action |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/resumeai/Dockerfile.template` | Created |\n| `apps/resumeai/lzc-manifest.yml` | Created |\n| `apps/resumeai/lzc-build.yml` | Created |\n| `apps/resumeai/lzc-deploy-params.yml` | Created |\n| `apps/resumeai/README.md` | Created |\n| `apps/resumeai/icon.png` | Created (placeholder 1×1 PNG) |\n| `registry/repos/resumeai.json` | Created |\n| `registry/repos/index.json` | Updated (added `resumeai.json`) |\n\n**Key decisions:**\n\n- **Port / service topology**: `web` (Next.js, port 3000) + `mongo` (MongoDB 7 sidecar). `web` uses `registry.lazycat.cloud/placeholder/resumeai:bootstrap`; `mongo` uses `mongo:7` directly — not the placeholder, per the rule against pointing sidecars at the built-app placeholder.\n- **MongoDB**: `mongodb://mongo:27017/resumeai` wired as a runtime env var; data persisted to `/lzcapp/var/db/resumeai/mongo`.\n- **Dockerfile.template**: Multi-stage Node 20 Alpine. Overwrites `next.config.mjs` at build time to enable `output: \"standalone\"` so the runner stage only needs the standalone bundle + static files. Build-time `ARG NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=` defaults to empty; Next.js App Router server components read this from `process.env` at runtime, so the real value injected via manifest env takes effect without a rebuild.\n- **Deploy params** (`lzc-deploy-params.yml`): captures `clerk_publishable_key`, `clerk_secret_key`, `gemini_api_key`, `login_user`, `login_password` — the manifest references them as `{{ index .U \"...\" }}`.\n- **Passwordless login**: `builtin://simple-inject-password` in `application.injects`. Clerk renders its sign-in form as standard HTML inputs at `/sign-in`, which the inject can target.\n- **check_strategy**: `commit_sha` — upstream's GitHub releases are Windows `.exe` installers, not Docker-compatible releases.\n- **image_targets**: `[\"web\"]` only — `mongo` is a stock sidecar with no build step.\n\n**Known limitation / risk:** The app requires a valid Clerk account (sign-up/sign-in) and a Google Gemini API key to be fully functional. Both are captured as deploy params. If the installation deploys without these, the browser verification phase will see Clerk initialization errors on the sign-in page. The README calls this out prominently and instructs the operator to create a Clerk app, add the LazyCat box domain to Clerk's allowed redirect URLs, and register a user account before relying on passwordless login."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":455,"cache_read_input_tokens":92528,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":455},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8885b858-35f1-4392-9afa-5fc75e8538ec","uuid":"531cf30e-7477-40e8-b40d-b0fa78688a85"}
